title: Modtro Relocates To Phillips Avenue
text:
Modtro Relocates To Phillips Avenue September 30, 2015, 5:18 PM SIOUX FALLS, SD - 
A new business is just hours from opening its doors on Phillips Avenue in downtown Sioux Falls. 
Modtro specializes in mid-century furniture, which is growing in popularity as people restore historic homes. 
"We're really excited about adding clients to our customer base. We have a large customer base now. Before we were a destination location and now that so many more people find out about it, it opens it up to so many more," Modtro Co-Owner Kyle Haug said. 
Modtro used to be located on North Main Avenue. The owners expect to see a lot more foot traffic at the new location. 
The new store is located right across the street from Zandbroz and will be open Thursday from 11 a.m to 7 p.m. Photo Credit:
